header
main
  .bound
    h1 KPCC Needs Your Help
    article
      h4 Dear Listener,
      p Even though KPCC was not targeted by the recent spate of credit card security breaches, we have been the unintended victim of them — and we've been harmed in a very real way. 
      p Thousands of KPCC supporters were issued new credit cards in the aftermath of the recent hacks. When that happened, their contributions to KPCC were inadvertently canceled. Thousands of lapsed pledges have resulted in significant loss in revenue. When your security was violated, our financial stability was also threatened. 
      p As the end of our fiscal year approaches, we’re doing everything in our power to minimize the harm. We've tightened our belts and clamped down on all of our expenditures.
      p Now we need your help to close the remaining gap, which equates to the production of a local program like AirTalk, or one of our award-winning news desks, like our environment or education desks.  
      p.always-be-closing This is something we’ve never encountered before. Your support is incredibly vital right now. We need 9,000 listeners to show their support by June 30th. Please <a href="https://scprcontribute.publicradio.org/contribute.php?refId=ctgpush">become a member, renew, or give an additional gift right now</a> and help us close this gap.
      p All good things (considered),
      p <strong>Bill Davis</strong> <br> President, Southern California Public Radio
